Overview

Step-by-step, to convert a folder of JPG/JPEG images into individual binary glTF or (.glb) files using Python.

The process:

Applies EXIF orientation so images are upright.
Converts image colors to sRGB (best-effort using ImageCms when available, or falls back to convert("RGB")).
Embeds the processed image bytes into a tiny GLB that contains a single textured plane scaled to the image aspect ratio.
Produces one .glb file per input image.

2. Requirements (what to install)

Python 3.7+
Pillow (for image handling and EXIF orientation)
Install: pip install pillow
Optional (recommended for color-managed conversions): Pillow with LCMS/ImageCms support
If your Pillow build includes ImageCms, it enables ICC-profile-aware conversions.
You can also provide an sRGB ICC file if you want explicit control (optional).

Example install commands:

pip install pillow

# Optional: if you have a system package for lcms2, reinstall Pillow so it builds with ImageCms:
# apt-get install liblcms2-dev  # Debian/Ubuntu (then reinstall pillow)
# pip install --force-reinstall --no-binary :all: pillow


3. Files & folders


Input folder: images/ (put your .jpg/.jpeg files here)
Output folder: out_glb/ (script will create this)

4. Quick run (one-line)
After you save the script as jpg_to_glb_srgb_full.py, run:

Without explicit ICC file:


python jpg_to_glb_srgb_full.py images out_glb

With an explicit sRGB ICC profile (optional):


python jpg_to_glb_srgb_full.py images out_glb /path/to/sRGB.icc

5. What the script does

Loads each JPG.
Uses ImageOps.exif_transpose() to apply EXIF orientation.
If ImageCms and an ICC profile are available, converts from the image's embedded profile (if present) to sRGB; otherwise uses convert("RGB").
Re-encodes the processed pixels to a JPEG buffer (so the bytes embedded in GLB match final pixels).
Builds a minimal glTF JSON describing a single mesh (a plane of correct aspect ratio), one material with baseColorTexture, and packs JSON + binary into GLB v2 binary format.
Writes one .glb per input image.
